The paper focuses on the power consumption of convolutional neural networks for keyword spotting, which falls under the categories of speech recognition (cs.SD), machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically uses convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision, but the application of keyword spotting is more closely related to speech recognition and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.SD, cs.LG, and cs.CL, followed by cs.NE and cs.CV.
